data.content:
## What Changed

.NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded to **Microsoft.OpenApi v2**, which targets OpenAPI 3.1. This is a major object-model rewrite:

| .NET 9 (OpenApi v1) | .NET 10 (OpenApi v2) |
|---|---|
| `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any.OpenApiString` | `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonValue` |
| `schema.Example = new OpenApiString(...)` | `schema.Example = JsonValue.Create(...)` |
| `schema.Nullable = true/false` | `schema.Type \|= JsonSchemaType.Null` |
| `OpenApiSecurityScheme { Reference = ... }` | `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference(id, ...)` |
| `new OpenApiSecurityRequirement { [scheme] = scopes }` | `new OpenApiSecurityRequirement { Schemes = ... }` |
| `ReferenceType.SecurityScheme` | Removed — use typed reference classes |

## Fixed Code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        // IOpenApiAny replaced by JsonNode
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    // Use OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference instead of OpenApiSecurityScheme + OpenApiReference
    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2");
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { Schemes = new Dictionary<OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference, IList<string>>
            {
                [oAuthScheme] = scopes
            }
        }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
            {
                // Nullable property removed; in OpenAPI 3.1, remove "null" from type flags
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;
            }
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of each fix:

1. **`OpenApiString` → `JsonValue.Create()`** — The `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace is gone; examples/defaults are now `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonNode`.

2. **Security scheme references** — Use the new `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference(id)` class (in `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References`) instead of manually constructing a `Reference` property.

3. **`SecurityRequirement`** — No longer acts as a dictionary itself; assign its `.Schemes` property instead.

4. **`Nullable` → `JsonSchemaType` flags** — OpenAPI 3.1 expresses nullability via the `type` array. Use bitwise operations on the `Type` enum (`|= JsonSchemaType.Null` to add, `&= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` to remove).
